Senate Banking Committee to Hold Hearing on FDIC, OCC Nominees

-- B y   G r e g o r y   M o t t
-- 
2011-07-20T19:30:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/senate-banking-committee-to-hold-hearing-on-fdic-occ-nominees.html
The U.S. Senate Banking Committee
will hold a hearing next week to consider the nominations of
Martin J. Gruenberg to become chairman of the Federal Deposit
Insurance Corp. and Thomas Curry as comptroller of the currency.  Gruenberg, who is serving as acting FDIC chairman, and
Curry, an FDIC board member, will testify at the July 26
hearing, Banking Committee spokesman Sean Oblack said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gregory Mott in Washington at 
 gmott1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lawrence Roberts at 
 lroberts13@bloomberg.net  